WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
I therefore, a prisoner for the Lord, urge you to walk in a manner worthy of the calling to which you have been called,

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.500
with all humility and gentleness, with patience, bearing with one another in love,

3
00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:16.000
eager to maintain the unity of the Spirit and the bond of peace.

4
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:21.000
There is one body and one Spirit, just as you were called to the one hope that belongs to your call,

5
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:26.000
one Lord, one faith, one baptism, one God and Father of all,

6
00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:33.000
who is over all and through all and in all, but grace was given to each one of us according to the measure of Christ's gift.

7
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:39.000
Therefore it says, when he ascended on high, he led a host of captives and he gave gifts to men.

8
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:45.000
In saying he ascended, what does it mean but that he had also descended into the lower regions, the earth?

9
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:52.000
He who descended is the one who also ascended far above all the heavens, that he might fill all the things.

10
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:58.000
And he gave the apostles, the prophets, the evangelists, the shepherds and teachers,

11
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:03.000
to equip the saints for the work of the ministry, for building up the body of Christ,

12
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:08.000
until we all attain to the unity of the faith and of the knowledge of the Son of God,

13
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
to mature manhood to the measure of the structure of the fullness of Christ,

14
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.000
so that we may no longer be children tossed to and fro by the waves and carried about by every wind of doctrine,

15
00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.000
by human cunning, by craftiness and deceitful schemes.

16
00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Rather speaking the truth in love, we are to grow up in every way into him who is the head, into Christ,

17
00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:33.000
from him the whole body, joined and held together by every joint to which is equipped,

18
00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:38.000
when each part is working properly, makes the body grow so that it fills itself up in love.

19
00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:39.000
This is the word of the Lord.

20
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:46.000
It's so good to be back together and it's good to be able to return to the book of Ephesians.

21
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:50.000
So, yeah, if you've got a Bible, do keep it open there at Ephesians

22
00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:54.000
or keep it in front of you there in your worship guide.

23
00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Julie and I have been away for the past couple of weeks,

24
00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:00.000
so when I talk about us being away or good to be back,

25
00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.000
we've been out of the country for a little bit.

26
00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:07.000
It was great to be in England and while we were there, we celebrated Christmas with family,

27
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:11.000
but we also went down to London to see the Lion King, to see the musical.

28
00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.000
And it was really amazing.

29
00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:14.000
We enjoyed that.

30
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:18.000
But if you've ever seen the Lion King, be it the musical or the movie,

31
00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:26.000
you'll know that everything kind of hangs on Simba, the Lion King, remembering who he is.

32
00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:32.000
And when he finally embraces who he truly is, he returns to his kingdom

33
00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
and it is all the better because of his return.

34
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.000
Well, here in the book of Ephesians, we saw in the first half

35
00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.000
that it is all about who Jesus truly is.

36
00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:49.000
But when we see who Jesus truly is, we can also find our own identity in him by being in him.

37
00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:51.000
We find our identity in Christ.

38
00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:56.000
But if you find your identity in Jesus, it will impact the way that you live.

39
00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:01.000
So who you are will be seen in how you live.

40
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:03.000
So that's what the second half is about.

41
00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:07.000
And you see that connected here in chapter 4 and verse 1.

42
00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:09.000
The first half is really those first three chapters.

43
00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.000
The last half is chapter 4 to 6.

44
00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:13.000
But chapter 4 verse 1 begins.

45
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:15.000
I therefore, a prisoner for the Lord,

46
00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:22.000
urge you to walk in a manner worthy of the calling to which you have been called.

47
00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:26.000
So he's saying, I therefore, on the basis of everything we've already seen

48
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:29.000
about what God has done for us in Christ,

49
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.000
urge you to walk in a manner worthy of your calling.

50
00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:40.000
So the calling he speaks of here is this calling of God for us to be in Christ.

51
00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:46.000
So if you put your faith in Christ, you've been made new in him.

52
00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:50.000
You've been united to him in his death and resurrection.

53
00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:55.000
You're part of the new humanity that God is creating called the church.

54
00:03:55.000 --> 00:04:01.000
This is the calling being spoken of here when God called us to himself in Christ.

55
00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:05.000
And if you're part of this new humanity in Christ,

56
00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:10.000
you need to hear this call to walk worthy of your calling.

57
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:16.000
So the walk being spoken of here is a is a continuous way of life.

58
00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
So if you're Christian, God has given you a new life in Christ,

59
00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
not so that you might merely exist in this new life,

60
00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:30.000
but that you might live the life that God has given you, the life that you were made for.

61
00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:34.000
He's laid out a path for you to walk now. Walk it.

62
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.000
And this morning we are particularly going to see though,

63
00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:41.000
is that we do not walk this path alone.

64
00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:48.000
The life that we were made for is designed to be lived together in community.

65
00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:54.000
We live in a culture that despite being more connected than ever through things like smartphones

66
00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:59.000
or social media is starved for authentic community.

67
00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:05.000
But the thing is that together life that people are longing for is fulfilled in Jesus.

68
00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:10.000
It's found in him and it is to be experienced in the life of the church,

69
00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:13.000
this community that God is creating.

70
00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Sadly churches don't always live this out.

71
00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:22.000
And even when churches are living this out, we can miss out on it personally.

72
00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:27.000
But what Paul writes here under the inspiration of God's Holy Spirit can be a real help to us.

73
00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:36.000
So for the next few moments I just want us to see three things that should characterize our life together as a church.

74
00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:38.000
So what is this life together all about?

75
00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:42.000
What should characterize it?

76
00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:47.000
Well first of all, our life together should be characterized by unity.

77
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:51.000
I recently heard something and I can't remember where I heard it,

78
00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.000
so it may very well have been from one of you.

79
00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
So forgive me for not quoting you if you told it to me.

80
00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:58.000
But it was about a guy who was stranded on a desert island

81
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:03.000
and he was out on this remote island, had been there for months and months and finally,

82
00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:06.000
people found out he was there and they went to rescue him and they came there

83
00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:09.000
and there he was with the three huts that he had built.

84
00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:12.000
And they said, well what are these three huts that you've built here?

85
00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:14.000
He said, well this one here is my house.

86
00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:16.000
And he said, and this one here is my church.

87
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.000
And they said, okay well what's the other hut?

88
00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:22.000
And he kind of looked over his shoulder, rolled his eyes and he said,

89
00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:24.000
that's the church I used to go to.

90
00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:29.000
So you can't have one church without having the other church that you don't speak to anymore.

91
00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:32.000
It's funny because there's a grain of truth there.

92
00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:40.000
Because instead of unity, all too often churches are marked by, or even scarred by, division.

93
00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:47.000
There may be times when a church forsakes the gospel and it's necessary to move away there.

94
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:51.000
But all too often it might be because people can't get along with each other

95
00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:54.000
even over the smallest of issues.

96
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:59.000
So walking this path together as the church requires unity.

97
00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:07.000
We are to be as Paul says in verse three, eager to maintain the unity of the spirit in the bond of peace.

98
00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:10.000
Now unity doesn't mean uniformity.

99
00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:15.000
The unity being spoken of here is unity in diversity.

100
00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:20.000
So in chapter three we saw that the church is made up of Jews and Gentiles alike.

101
00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.000
We are part of one body.

102
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:27.000
So no matter what your ethnic background is, we are part of this one body together.

103
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:34.000
And here we see, Paul's going to add to this, that the church is also made up of all different types of members with different gifts.

104
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:41.000
So God is weaving together this beautiful tapestry of all different sorts of people from different ethnic backgrounds,

105
00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:45.000
cultures, classes, ages, personalities, different gifts.

106
00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:51.000
We are diverse but God is uniting us together in Christ.

107
00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:58.000
And the question is, well how do we live out this unity in diversity in practice?

108
00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:01.000
Well it's going to involve at least a couple of things.

109
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:06.000
It's going to involve what we might call our position and our disposition.

110
00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:11.000
So it's knowing that we are united, that's our position,

111
00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:17.000
and then making the effort to live like we are actually united together in Christ.

112
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:21.000
If it helps, maybe think of a three-legged race.

113
00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:23.000
I don't know if you ever did that in field days growing up.

114
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:27.000
I remember when I was a little kid, you'd go and you'd line up

115
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:31.000
and normally in a race you'd just kind of take off running and it's all down to you and how fast you can run.

116
00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:36.000
But in the three-legged race you're paired with somebody and they get like a velcro strap and it strap you both together.

117
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:44.000
And you can't just take off running, you've got to learn to walk together and then to run together to try to win the race together.

118
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:46.000
And so this is what we have here.

119
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:51.000
So we have been united together in Christ so we already are joins together.

120
00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:55.000
Now we must learn to walk together in Him.

121
00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.000
Alright so our position, we are one.

122
00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:00.000
We've been united together in Jesus.

123
00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:07.000
The German pastor Dietrich Bonhoeffer wrote a little book on Christian community called Life Together.

124
00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:11.000
And I totally stole the name for the title for this sermon this morning.

125
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:13.000
But it's a great little book and I would encourage you to read it.

126
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:16.000
But he wrote something striking about Christian community in it.

127
00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:21.000
He said this, he said, Christian community is not an ideal we have to realize,

128
00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:28.000
but rather a reality created by God and Christ in which we may participate.

129
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:31.000
Right so it already exists we don't create it.

130
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:35.000
But we can participate in this Christian community.

131
00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:41.000
So in a moment we're going to see yes unity is something we have to work on but it's first something that is given to us already.

132
00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.000
We already have it. We're already united.

133
00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.000
We're already one.

134
00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:50.000
And so Paul drives this home here repeating the word one seven times.

135
00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:53.000
Do you see it in the passage? He says one over and over again.

136
00:09:53.000 --> 00:10:03.000
There is one body, one spirit, one hope, one Lord, one faith, one baptism, one God and Father of all.

137
00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:09.000
And he's writing this in a way that's showing us where our communal life together,

138
00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:12.000
our common life together as the church comes from.

139
00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:21.000
And it comes from the triune nature of our God who is Father, Son and Holy Spirit.

140
00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:28.000
So you see that our unity comes from the unity of God, this one God who exists in three persons.

141
00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
So do you see the Holy Spirit present here and how he phrases this?

142
00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:35.000
So he says there's one body and one spirit.

143
00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:42.000
So you personally, you are not just a body. You're a unity of both body and spirit.

144
00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:51.000
So in a similar way, the church, the body of Christ has one animating spirit, the Holy Spirit of God.

145
00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:56.000
So the same spirit of God gives life to everyone who puts their faith in Christ.

146
00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:02.000
So if you belong to Christ, the Holy Spirit of God dwells in you and the person next to you and the person over here.

147
00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:06.000
The same spirit dwells in all of us.

148
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:08.000
We're in Christ part of his church.

149
00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:11.000
That's the Holy Spirit. But you also see the sun here.

150
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:14.000
See this in verse five. There is one Lord.

151
00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:26.000
Now this is Jesus. If you go back to chapter one of Ephesians, we already saw that Jesus is the one who is now seated at God's right hand in heavenly places far above all things.

152
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:29.000
He is the head of the church.

153
00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:35.000
When it speaks here of the one faith, this is the body of doctrine that tells us about who he truly is.

154
00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:39.000
This is who we are called to trust in.

155
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:44.000
We are united to him in one baptism as well. It mentions here.

156
00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:49.000
So by the spirit of God, we are baptized into Christ.

157
00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:55.000
So we're united to him by faith. We're united to him in his death and in his resurrection.

158
00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:59.000
And that is the baptism that we share by the spirits.

159
00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:03.000
We're baptized into Christ. We're united to him.

160
00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:11.000
And this is then reflected, this inward reality, this inward spiritual reality is of course reflected in water baptism as well.

161
00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:15.000
Showing that we are united to Christ in his death and in his resurrection.

162
00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.000
So it's pointing us to the sun here.

163
00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:27.000
We're pointing to the Father because there is, verse six, one God and Father of all who is over all and through all and in all.

164
00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:32.000
So the ground of our unity with each other is the unity of the triune God.

165
00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:41.000
God is one and yet he exists in this loving, eternal community of three persons, Father, Son and Spirit.

166
00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:46.000
So John 17, Jesus prays for the unity of the church.

167
00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:54.000
And here's how he prays for his father. Keep them in your name that they may be one even as we are one.

168
00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:57.000
So in Christ we are one.

169
00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:59.000
But unity is also something we have to work on.

170
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:05.000
We're told here to be eager or to be diligent to maintain our unity.

171
00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:07.000
So you might think of it this way.

172
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:11.000
If you're born into a family, they're your family, whether you like it or not.

173
00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:18.000
But it's a lot better to get on with your family and to work on living together as one loving family.

174
00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:22.000
So it's true, like if you are in Christ, you are part of the family of God.

175
00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:28.000
So we are united in that sense, but that doesn't mean that we don't fall out and kind of try to keep our distance from each other.

176
00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:31.000
So there's another sense in which we've got to work on unity.

177
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:34.000
It has to be maintained.

178
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:38.000
It begins with our disposition towards one another.

179
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:45.000
We got our position. We are united. Our disposition, if I can get it out, is here too.

180
00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:50.000
So Paul lists out a number of character qualities. I wonder if you saw them in verse two.

181
00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:54.000
And these are character qualities that foster practical unity.

182
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:58.000
But interestingly, all of them are inward qualities.

183
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:01.000
They deal with the tone of the church.

184
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:06.000
You might say the vibe of the church, our relationships.

185
00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:10.000
Like what do they give off here? It's what's going on inwardly.

186
00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:15.000
So notice what we're invited to. Humility is where it starts.

187
00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:17.000
So humility is a lowliness of mind.

188
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:24.000
It's instead of having a high view of ourselves, we humble ourselves before God and with others too.

189
00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:31.000
When it comes to the church, we come with an attentiveness to others, putting them before ourselves.

190
00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:33.000
He then talks about gentleness.

191
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:38.000
So instead of treating one another harshly, we deal with one another graciously and kindly.

192
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.000
And sometimes that may take restraint.

193
00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:47.000
But unity can only be fostered through gentleness towards one another.

194
00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:53.000
He also talks about patience, even bearing with one another.

195
00:14:53.000 --> 00:15:01.000
These character traits aren't always easy because everyone we interact with doesn't necessarily come into it with humility and gentleness.

196
00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:04.000
We will encounter the opposite. We'll encounter pride in one another.

197
00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:07.000
We'll encounter harshness in one another sometimes.

198
00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:10.000
And so we have to be patient with one another.

199
00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:18.000
It's interesting that word bearing has mixed in with the idea of putting up with someone who's annoying.

200
00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:23.000
Alright, so there's a real honesty that is here in what is said.

201
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:29.000
So just because someone is rude to us or whatever, that doesn't give us the right to strike back.

202
00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:39.000
God is patiently at work in them and he can give us the patience to walk alongside them, even to bear with them.

203
00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:45.000
But I don't want to give you the wrong impression with bearing because notice what it's followed up with, bearing with them in love.

204
00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:51.000
So we don't bear with them begrudgingly, like really gritting our teeth and rolling our eyes and talking behind their back or something.

205
00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:57.000
It's not like that. We bear with them because God has given us His love for them.

206
00:15:57.000 --> 00:16:02.000
We know He loves them. We know that we're sinful people and He loves us anyway.

207
00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:07.000
And so we love them because they are part of this one body with us.

208
00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:12.000
So unity doesn't ultimately come from the right practices but from the right posture.

209
00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:17.000
That's where it starts. A posture of love.

210
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:21.000
So God unites us and gives us this desire to be with one another.

211
00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:25.000
And the unity we're called to is ultimately the unity of the Spirit.

212
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:28.000
It's what the Spirit of God is doing in our midst.

213
00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:32.000
Okay, so our life together should be characterized by unity.

214
00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:37.000
But also secondly, as we move on we see it should be characterized as well by ministry.

215
00:16:37.000 --> 00:16:42.000
Our life together is a life of ministry.

216
00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:49.000
I don't know if you saw any of the funeral of President Jimmy Carter this past week.

217
00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:52.000
There's lots of interesting elements of it.

218
00:16:52.000 --> 00:16:56.000
But one of them was just to see the Secret Service detail walking alongside the hearse.

219
00:16:56.000 --> 00:17:01.000
And members of the Secret Service always have different code names for different presidents they work with.

220
00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:04.000
And I wonder if you heard the code name for Jimmy Carter.

221
00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:07.000
The code name was Deacon.

222
00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:12.000
So they called him Deacon because of his commitment to his Christian faith.

223
00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:15.000
That came through as they called him Deacon.

224
00:17:15.000 --> 00:17:21.000
And the word Deacon is the word that is used for ministry in verse 12.

225
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:25.000
So notice this. It says that we are called to the work of the ministry.

226
00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:28.000
We are equipped for the work of the ministry.

227
00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:30.000
It's the same word that's used for Deacons.

228
00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:35.000
People who are called to lead in particular areas of ministry or service.

229
00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:39.000
But it's a service that we are all called to.

230
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:42.000
We're all called to minister to one another.

231
00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.000
So notice how we're all called to it.

232
00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:50.000
So in verse 7, although there's one church, there's a diversity of gifts that are given.

233
00:17:50.000 --> 00:17:54.000
They're given to each one of us that we might serve.

234
00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:59.000
So if Christ has graciously gifted all of us one implication is that we're all called to serve.

235
00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:03.000
We're all called to serve one another with a gift that he has given us.

236
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:09.000
Verse 12, you see that the work of the ministry isn't sort of given to the quote unquote professionals.

237
00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:12.000
It's given to every single believer.

238
00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:19.000
Verse 16, we see that churches work best when every member is working properly.

239
00:18:19.000 --> 00:18:24.000
So every member is called to be a minister, so to speak.

240
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:26.000
So the churches always operate in this way.

241
00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:29.000
Well, unfortunately, the answer is sometimes no.

242
00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:37.000
I've heard churches compared to soccer games where you have 22,000 spectators desperately in need of exercise,

243
00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:41.000
watching 22 players desperately in need of rest.

244
00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:44.000
I don't know if you've ever been a part of a church where that's the case.

245
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:49.000
We've got a handful of people doing a lot and a lot of people just kind of turning up.

246
00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:52.000
The church is not a spectator sport.

247
00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:57.000
Now, there could be all sorts of reasons why it ends up becoming that way in particular instances.

248
00:18:57.000 --> 00:19:04.000
You might have leaders holding on to things rather than enlisting and equipping and involving others in ministries.

249
00:19:04.000 --> 00:19:09.000
Other times an issue can be a lack of willingness or initiative from members who should be involved.

250
00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:11.000
And there could be other factors at work too.

251
00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:14.000
And oftentimes there's a number of things at work.

252
00:19:14.000 --> 00:19:16.000
But that's not how it's supposed to be.

253
00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:19.000
We're all called to the work of the ministry.

254
00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:30.000
Can I just say that having lived overseas for 14 years, there's something that stands out about churches in the U.S. in particular.

255
00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:33.000
And I'm happy for you to take me to task on this if you would like to.

256
00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:38.000
But it's what I might call it the professionalization of ministry.

257
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:39.000
What do I mean by that?

258
00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:52.000
What I mean is that American churches are far quicker to move past depending on every member ministry to hire staff to carry out the work of the ministry.

259
00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:59.000
Now, what I don't mean by that, I don't mean like, oh, churches should never hire staff or we don't believe in that kind of thing.

260
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:05.000
There's sometimes when that is good and necessary and the right call to make 100%.

261
00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:14.000
At the same time, we need to be aware of the danger of developing a consumer culture where we come to church to receive the work of the ministry.

262
00:20:14.000 --> 00:20:18.000
We're kind of paying for the goods and we hope to get the goods.

263
00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:20.000
You see what I'm saying?

264
00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:26.000
We're all called to participate in the building of the body.

265
00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:29.000
So the work is for all of us.

266
00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:30.000
It isn't easy.

267
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:34.000
You might say, well, ministry, I'm not sure if I'm kitted out and ready for ministry.

268
00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:38.000
Well, the good news is it's a work that we are also all equipped for.

269
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:41.000
So we're all called to it and equipped for ministry.

270
00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:43.000
Where do we see that here?

271
00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:48.000
So verse seven, Christ equips us by His grace.

272
00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:51.000
You look in Mark chapter 10 and verse 45.

273
00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:57.000
We see that the Son of man came not to be served, but to serve and to give His life as a ransom for many.

274
00:20:57.000 --> 00:21:05.000
And it is this Christ who provides all that we need to serve others the way that He did.

275
00:21:05.000 --> 00:21:16.000
And in verse seven, we see that Christ gives us the exact grace that we need to use the specific gifts and opportunities that He has given us to fulfill our ministry.

276
00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:23.000
Then He goes on in verses eight to ten to make the case for how Christ does this.

277
00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:27.000
He says He points to the humility and exaltation of Jesus.

278
00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:35.000
So in order to accomplish His redemptive plan, Christ descended into this world and even into death.

279
00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:41.000
But then He rises again victorious and ascends to His heavenly throne, having triumphed over His enemies.

280
00:21:41.000 --> 00:21:43.000
And when He ascended, what do we read here?

281
00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:46.000
It says He gave gifts to men.

282
00:21:46.000 --> 00:21:49.000
He ascended that He might fill all things.

283
00:21:49.000 --> 00:22:02.000
So when He ascended to His heavenly throne, from which He reigns over all things, He gave gifts to His church so that we might carry out His work in the world.

284
00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:12.000
So today, one of the ways that Christ is accomplishing His good purposes in the world is by empowering His people by His grace to serve others.

285
00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:16.000
So the one who reigns over everything right now, how can we see His reign?

286
00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:23.000
How can we know that Christ is reigning in heaven because He has provided what we need to serve one another.

287
00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:32.000
And as we serve one another by His grace and for His glory, His reign is made visible in the life of the church.

288
00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:34.000
So He's given us what we need.

289
00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:36.000
And He's the one who's able to do that.

290
00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:42.000
But another way He does this, interestingly, in verse 12, we see that He has also given the church leaders.

291
00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:48.000
So leaders are given to the church to equip the whole body for the work of the ministry.

292
00:22:48.000 --> 00:22:54.000
And once again, it's not that they are called to do the work of the ministry and we are called to receive the work of the ministry.

293
00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:56.000
There's not a kind of sharp division there.

294
00:22:56.000 --> 00:23:04.000
We're all involved in the work of the ministry, but there's a particular responsibility of leaders to equip the whole body for the work of the ministry.

295
00:23:05.000 --> 00:23:10.000
Equip was a medical term that was actually used to set a bone.

296
00:23:10.000 --> 00:23:16.000
I don't know if you've ever had to have a bone set in place, but that was where it was used at the time.

297
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:24.000
So you might say that leaders are guiding members of the body to take their place in the work of the ministry and helping them to do that.

298
00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:26.000
That's the responsibility of leaders.

299
00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:32.000
It was also a word that was used in a different context to talk about furnishing a house.

300
00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:42.000
Okay, so you might say this, that the ministry of leaders is providing what we need to develop church members that we might build one another up in Christ.

301
00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:48.000
It's providing what we need so that we're able to minister to others as we're called to.

302
00:23:48.000 --> 00:23:56.000
So what did leaders equip the church with so that the church might minister one to another?

303
00:23:56.000 --> 00:24:03.000
Well, there's a hint of what these leaders give in the types of leaders that are listed here.

304
00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:05.000
You notice there are five leaders.

305
00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:07.000
So you've got apostles.

306
00:24:07.000 --> 00:24:09.000
So let's do a quick run through.

307
00:24:09.000 --> 00:24:17.000
Apostles are these foundational leaders in the life of the church who are appointed and sent out by Christ as his authoritative spokesman.

308
00:24:17.000 --> 00:24:19.000
So that's the apostles.

309
00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.000
And you've got the prophets.

310
00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:26.000
These were also foundational leaders that brought God's words to the church.

311
00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:28.000
And you've got evangelists.

312
00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:29.000
These are gospel preachers.

313
00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:35.000
They're proclaiming Jesus to people who have never heard about him before that they're devoting themselves to that.

314
00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:37.000
And you've got shepherds.

315
00:24:37.000 --> 00:24:46.000
So shepherds are pastors or leaders of the church who care for Christ's flock in local churches primarily through their teaching.

316
00:24:46.000 --> 00:24:48.000
And then you've got listed teachers.

317
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:56.000
It's interesting there's a bit of a discussion as to whether or not shepherds and teachers or pastors and teachers are just referring to the same person or whether or not it's two separate things.

318
00:24:56.000 --> 00:25:00.000
Because the responsibility of a pastor is to teach the church.

319
00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:06.000
But also you can have other people who are teachers teaching the church who aren't necessarily pastors.

320
00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:09.000
So I think there is some space for separating those out as well.

321
00:25:09.000 --> 00:25:14.000
But what all of these five types of leaders have in common?

322
00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:17.000
What do you see there?

323
00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:21.000
All of their ministries are word based.

324
00:25:21.000 --> 00:25:26.000
So how do they equip the church by bringing the word of God to the church?

325
00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:29.000
So every member needs to hear the word of God.

326
00:25:29.000 --> 00:25:36.000
And it's in the word of God that we are equipped with all that we need for the service that he has called us to.

327
00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:45.000
So 2 Timothy 3 in verse 17 says that it is scripture that furnishes us with everything that we need for every good work.

328
00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:47.000
It's like our physical bodies.

329
00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:51.000
Food matters to your entire body.

330
00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:53.000
No matter what part of the body you're thinking about.

331
00:25:53.000 --> 00:25:56.000
Like food plays a part in that ultimately.

332
00:25:56.000 --> 00:26:00.000
So just like physical food matters to every part of our physical body.

333
00:26:00.000 --> 00:26:09.000
So the spiritual nourishment of the word is necessary for every member of Christ's body, the church.

334
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:14.000
So we all need to be equipped and shaped by the word of God.

335
00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:21.000
And every ministry that we are involved in must be directed and governed by the word of God.

336
00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:25.000
God does his work through his word.

337
00:26:25.000 --> 00:26:33.000
So Christ gives every one of us the gifts we need and equips us by his word that we might serve one another in the church.

338
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:36.000
So the final point I want to consider is this.

339
00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:39.000
It's really why we serve.

340
00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:51.000
So our life together is characterized by unity, by ministry, and that is then for the purpose of maturity.

341
00:26:51.000 --> 00:26:57.000
So we've been brought together that we might grow together in maturity.

342
00:26:57.000 --> 00:27:02.000
I don't know if you've done this at home, but I know some parents or grandparents will have like a doorpost in their house.

343
00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:07.000
When their child is growing up, they'll kind of like mark how high the child is, how tall they are.

344
00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:11.000
Keep marking that you can look back and they were this height, this height, this height, this height.

345
00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:17.000
So here in verse 13 we're given a measure of our maturity as the church.

346
00:27:17.000 --> 00:27:22.000
So how do you measure the maturity of a church, the growth of a church?

347
00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:24.000
It says this.

348
00:27:24.000 --> 00:27:32.000
So we carry on in the work of the ministry, building up the body of Christ until we all attain to the unity of the faith

349
00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:36.000
and of the knowledge of the Son of God to mature manhood.

350
00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:38.000
Here's the measure.

351
00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:44.000
To the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ.

352
00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:47.000
So what's the measure of a church?

353
00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:50.000
Is it the number of attendees?

354
00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:52.000
Is it the number of baptisms?

355
00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:55.000
Is it the percentage of members serving as volunteers?

356
00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:58.000
Is it financial stability?

357
00:27:58.000 --> 00:27:59.000
What is it?

358
00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:07.000
Those are all good things, but they are not the measure of the success of a church.

359
00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:11.000
There was one measure that comes to the success of the church.

360
00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:13.000
There's one measure that God is using.

361
00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:14.000
What is it?

362
00:28:14.000 --> 00:28:20.000
It's the stature of the fullness of Christ.

363
00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:28.000
So we don't need to go to a whiteboard here in January to figure out what is our goal together as Trinity Fellowship for 2025.

364
00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:29.000
What's it going to be this year?

365
00:28:29.000 --> 00:28:32.000
Because we have already been given the goal.

366
00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:35.000
Christ is the goal.

367
00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:37.000
He is the measure.

368
00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:46.000
So we've been brought together that we might know more and more of Him and that we might grow together in His likeness.

369
00:28:46.000 --> 00:28:51.000
And as we grow in His likeness, we bear witness to the world around us.

370
00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:54.000
This is who Jesus is.

371
00:28:54.000 --> 00:28:58.000
So Christ's likeness is the measure of a church.

372
00:28:58.000 --> 00:29:04.000
The thing is you can be sort of successful or impressive looking in other areas,

373
00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:10.000
but if we fail in this area of Christ's likeness, then we've failed.

374
00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:13.000
And there is a real danger that we face.

375
00:29:13.000 --> 00:29:20.000
And Paul draws our attention after mentioning that Christ's likeness is the aim here, knowing Christ, that there's a danger we face.

376
00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:22.000
So verse 14.

377
00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:28.000
What is it? If we don't grow up in Christ, we will be like children tossed to and fro by the wind and the waves

378
00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:34.000
and carried about by every wind of doctrine, by human cunning, by craftiness in deceitful schemes.

379
00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:44.000
In other words, if we don't grow up in Christ, we are susceptible to be drawn away from what Paul refers to as the truth that is in Jesus.

380
00:29:44.000 --> 00:29:57.000
So there's new ways of thinking and living that are always put before us, and they can distract us and even draw us away from the word of life.

381
00:29:57.000 --> 00:30:00.000
They can draw us away even from Christ.

382
00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:07.000
So if we're not mature in Christ, we're susceptible to the deception that is in the world.

383
00:30:07.000 --> 00:30:11.000
We'll be tossed to and fro, gullible to lies.

384
00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:21.000
So we face a danger if we don't know the truth that's in Christ, if we're not growing up in Him to look elsewhere.

385
00:30:21.000 --> 00:30:24.000
But also we see it not just negatively but positively.

386
00:30:24.000 --> 00:30:26.000
He shows us how we grow in Christ's likeness.

387
00:30:26.000 --> 00:30:29.000
Now, the Lord is the one who builds His church.

388
00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:36.000
Matthew 16, 18. Jesus said, I will build my church. It belongs to Him. He's the one who builds us.

389
00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:42.000
But here we see that He also uses us in the building of His church.

390
00:30:42.000 --> 00:30:47.000
In verse 16, we see that the body builds itself up in love.

391
00:30:47.000 --> 00:30:53.000
So how does that happen? How does God use us to build His church?

392
00:30:53.000 --> 00:31:01.000
The answer put simply is, when the truth is spoken in love, by speaking the truth in love.

393
00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:11.000
So we grow in Christ's likeness when the truth of God's Word is proclaimed in the context of loving relationships in the church.

394
00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:17.000
So when we're speaking the truth to one another, doing so from a place of genuine love for one another.

395
00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:20.000
Both of those things need to be present simultaneously.

396
00:31:20.000 --> 00:31:22.000
So there's two ditches to avoid here.

397
00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:31.000
We need to avoid the mistake of avoiding or soft peddling the hard truths of God's Word and saying,

398
00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:38.000
well, we really want to be a loving church so we don't want to get into those doctrinal issues that might divide us.

399
00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:40.000
But there's another ditch to avoid as well.

400
00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:47.000
And that is like holding fast to the right doctrine and being proud of how right we are in what we believe

401
00:31:47.000 --> 00:31:57.000
and not having a loving environment for people to come to where we genuinely love them and walk alongside them as we grow together in Christ.

402
00:31:57.000 --> 00:32:05.000
So a church that is growing in Christ's likeness is a church where both truth and love are present.

403
00:32:05.000 --> 00:32:09.000
It's in the truth of God's Word that we come to see more of Jesus.

404
00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:21.000
And as we grow up in him, the love of Jesus who laid down his life for us will be seen as we lay down our own lives for others around us.

405
00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:35.000
So whatever else happens in the life of this church this year, whatever results we see or do not see, let's determine by God's grace to pursue Christ above all else

406
00:32:35.000 --> 00:32:40.000
and pray that we might grow in his likeness.

407
00:32:40.000 --> 00:32:47.000
So just in conclusion, this together life that we were made for is found in Jesus.

408
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:48.000
So how should we respond?

409
00:32:48.000 --> 00:32:52.000
So what does that mean for me like over the next few weeks?

410
00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:55.000
What does that mean for you over the next few weeks?

411
00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:56.000
Three quick things.

412
00:32:56.000 --> 00:33:00.000
One is come to Christ.

413
00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:12.000
So if you're longing for community, that longing is ultimately fulfilled in coming to Jesus and coming to know God through him.

414
00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:15.000
You will be disappointed by the church.

415
00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:20.000
You will even be disappointed by this church.

416
00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:22.000
But Christ is not disappointed.

417
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:28.000
And we can know his love when we come to him by faith.

418
00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:36.000
And then when we come to him by faith, we're then invited to participate in this growing community project called the church.

419
00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:38.000
So first of all, come to Christ.

420
00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:46.000
And then secondly, come to church to just put it simply come to church.

421
00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:52.000
Church is of course who we are more than what we go to.

422
00:33:52.000 --> 00:34:05.000
But if we're going to receive what God has for us and to give to others what he's given us to give to them, we've got to be present with one another.

423
00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:10.000
I heard an interview with Tom Hanks, that great theologian.

424
00:34:10.000 --> 00:34:16.000
And he said, you know, sometimes I'm asked about different different characters I've done.

425
00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:22.000
He's like, so Forrest Gump, people ask me like, how did you create this particular like magical scene with Forrest Gump?

426
00:34:22.000 --> 00:34:25.000
Like, how did you do that? What is the secret?

427
00:34:25.000 --> 00:34:27.000
He said, do you want to know the secret?

428
00:34:27.000 --> 00:34:30.000
I'll tell you this trick.

429
00:34:30.000 --> 00:34:32.000
I go there.

430
00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:34.000
He said, the secret is go there.

431
00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:38.000
He's like, some days when I go to work, I don't feel like going to work.

432
00:34:38.000 --> 00:34:42.000
I feel really sad and I've got to go act out this really happy scene.

433
00:34:42.000 --> 00:34:47.000
But I turn up and sometimes things happen that people say are magical.

434
00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:56.000
He's like, sometimes I feel great and I've got to go act out this sad scene, but it's in going there that these things happen.

435
00:34:56.000 --> 00:35:00.000
So it's not terrible advice for church life.

436
00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:06.000
I don't know about you, but I don't always feel like turning up.

437
00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:08.000
I don't.

438
00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:19.000
But God is creating something beautiful in the life of His church and you won't experience it if you're not present with other believers in the life of the church.

439
00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:22.000
And I don't just be coming to Sunday services to that.

440
00:35:22.000 --> 00:35:23.000
That's part of it.

441
00:35:23.000 --> 00:35:30.000
That gathering with others maybe in a home group or or informally throughout the week just going and spending time with one another.

442
00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:37.000
But be present to one another that we might hear the truth and receive the love and grow together in Jesus' likeness.

443
00:35:37.000 --> 00:35:39.000
Let's make it a priority.

444
00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:44.000
And thirdly, so come to Christ, come to church and get involved.

445
00:35:44.000 --> 00:35:52.000
If the body of Christ grows when every member is involved in ministry, then that means you're needed.

446
00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:55.000
Like we really need you here.

447
00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:57.000
You matter.

448
00:35:57.000 --> 00:36:01.000
Every single one of you matters.

449
00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:12.000
You are part of what God is doing here to grow us in the likeness of Jesus and bring him glory in the world.

450
00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:15.000
So serve one another in the grace that he supplies.

451
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:17.000
Let's pray.

452
00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:22.000
Lord, it is such a privilege to be part of your family.

453
00:36:22.000 --> 00:36:28.000
It's a Lord I pray that you would help us by your grace to live out this calling.

454
00:36:28.000 --> 00:36:32.000
Lord, we thank you for bringing us to yourself.

455
00:36:32.000 --> 00:36:41.000
And Lord, I pray that you would give us a growing desire to be with you, but also a growing desire to be with one another.

456
00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:47.000
Lord, as we are with one another, Lord, I pray that we would increase in our love for one another.

457
00:36:47.000 --> 00:36:52.000
And Lord, we would have an eye to how we might serve one another.

458
00:36:52.000 --> 00:37:07.000
Lord, whatever you have in store for us over the coming months, over this coming year, Lord, I pray that we will be more like Jesus than we were when we began.

459
00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:15.000
So we pray that you would accomplish your work for your glory in Jesus' name. Amen.

